The '''Mundart des Ostgebiets''' is a [[subdialect]] of [[Low Prussian]], a dialect of [[Low German]].  It was spoken around Insterburg (now [[Chernyakhovsk]], [[Russia]]), the Memel ([[Klaipėda]], [[Lithuania]]), and [[Tilsit]] ([[Sovyetsk]], [[Russia]]). Many speakers of this subdialect were [[Prussian Lithuanians]].

