'''Nina Hyams''' (born 1952) is a full professor of [[linguistics]] at the [[University of California in Los Angeles]]. Her primary research area is [[grammatical]] development in [[first language acquisition]]<ref name="Anderson2004">{{cite book|last=Anderson|first=John Robert|title=Cognitive psychology and its implications|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9P4p6eAULMoC&pg=PA384|accessdate=28 June 2011|date=October 2004|publisher=Macmillan|isbn=978-0-7167-0110-1|pages=384–}}</ref><ref name="JosephJanda2003">{{cite book|last1=Joseph|first1=Brian D.|last2=Janda|first2=Richard D.|title=The handbook of historical linguistics|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uNSxFdbSmDgC&pg=PA500|accessdate=28 June 2011|year=2003|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|isbn=978-0-631-19571-9|pages=500–}}</ref><ref name="White2003">{{cite book|last=White|first=Lydia|title=Second language acquisition and universal grammar|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2Q25nuAQ-oQC&pg=PR11|accessdate=28 June 2011|date=2003-03-24|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-79647-7|pages=194–}}</ref><ref name="CookNewson2007">{{cite book|last1=Cook|first1=Vivian James|last2=Newson|first2=Mark|title=Chomsky's universal grammar: an introduction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mguunu3sI-YC&pg=PA213|accessdate=28 June 2011|year=2007|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|isbn=978-1-4051-1187-4|pages=213–}}</ref><ref name="ChamberlainMorford2000">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F5R94AGV7wAC&pg=PA91|title=Language acquisition by eye|last2=Morford|first2=Jill Patterson|first3=Rachel I.|publisher=Psychology Press|year=2000|isbn=978-0-8058-2937-2|location=|pages=91–95|last1=Chamberlain|first1=Charlene|author2-link=Jill Morford|last3=Mayberry|accessdate=28 June 2011}}</ref><ref name="LustHermon1994">{{cite book|last1=Lust|first1=Barbara|last2=Hermon|first2=Gabriella|last3=Kornfilt|first3=Jaklin|title=Syntactic Theory and First Language Acquisition: Cross-Linguistic Perspectives : Binding, Dependencies, and Learnability|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=unOF3RtBbmcC&pg=PA15|accessdate=28 June 2011|date=1994-12-13|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-8058-1350-0|pages=15–}}</ref> and is noted for her research into the acquisition of [[null subjects]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CJPYxRQgZpEC&pg=PA245&dq=%22Nina+Hyams%22+linguistics#v=onepage&q=Nina%20Hyams&f=false|title=Current issues in generative Hebrew linguistics|isbn= 978-90-272-5517-4|author=Sharon Armon-Lotem|author2=Gabi Danon |author3=Susan Deborah Rothstein |year=2008}}</ref><ref name="Radford2010">{{cite book|last=Radford|first=|title=An Introduction to English Sentence Structure International Student Edition|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EUwDUJWtBmIC&pg=PA36|accessdate=28 June 2011|date=2010-02-25|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-15730-8|pages=36–}}</ref><ref name="Jaeggli1989">{{cite book|last=Jaeggli|first=Osvaldo|title=The Null subject parameter|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WfdzrEbIaeQC&pg=PA26|accessdate=28 June 2011|date=1989-05-31|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-1-55608-087-6|pages=26–}}</ref>

